 :EndIf

 :If action‚Č°'data' ‚ćĚ This is a generic data-storage property usable on any control
     ‚ćĚ This does not bother to use Dyalog's Data property, but just stores the value in a namespace variable
     :If √ó‚ČĘargs ‚ćĚ If we have new data, write it
         :If 1=‚ČĘargs ‚čĄ args‚Üź‚äÉargs ‚čĄ :EndIf ‚ćĚ If only a single item is provided, assume it is unnested
         obj._data‚Üźargs
         result‚ÜźClasses.NoRes
     :Else ‚ćĚ Otherwise just read it (default=0)
         result‚Üźobj ‚éēVGET‚äā'_data' 0
     :EndIf
 :EndIf

 :If '‚ąÜ'=‚äÉaction ‚ćĚ UDP processing
     :If 0‚ąä‚ČĘargs ‚ćĚ Reading a UDP
         result‚Üźobj ‚éēVGET‚äā('_',action)0 ‚ćĚ Read current value with a standard default of scalar 0
     :Else ‚ćĚ Assigning a UDP
         :If 1=‚ČĘargs ‚čĄ args‚Üź‚äÉargs ‚čĄ :EndIf ‚ćĚ Single values should be scalar
         :If args‚Č°0 ‚ćĚ If it's being set back to default, then that's basically an erasure
             obj.‚éēEX'_',action ‚ćĚ Just keep it neat
         :Else
             obj ‚éēVSET‚äā('_',action)args ‚ćĚ Set the new value
